The course promotes conceptualisation of  interdisciplinarity. This course focuses on developing 21st century skills (including problem solving, reasoned decision making and critical thinking). During the course, 6-8 everyday life-related interdisciplinary modules will be introduced and analysed. This course also includes inquiry-based experimentation and seeks to develop transformative skills.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) to give an overview about interdisciplinary learning in science education;
2) to develop skills to identify and formulate science-related problems;
3) to introduce interdisciplinary thinking for solving science-related problems;
4) to develop skills to create and carry out inquiry-based  investigations;
5) to develop skills to make reasoned decisions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) is able to put forward reasoned examples of interdisciplinary learning in science education;
2) is able to identify and formulate science-related problems;
3) comprehends the importance of interdisciplinary thinking and is able to apply this while solving science-related problems;
4) is able to create and carry out inquiry-based investigations for solving science-related problems;
5) is able to make reasoned, socio-scientific decisions.
